# Routine — {{AGENT_NAME}}

Run **{{AGENT_NAME}}** on a schedule from Anthropic-managed cloud infra. Draws
down your subscription usage — **no API key**. (Research preview.)

## Config

| Field | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Name | {{AGENT_NAME}} |
| Prompt | Use the {{AGENT_NAME}} agent to {{TASK}}. Use relative dates ("today"). |
| Model | {{sonnet \| opus \| haiku}} |
| Repository | {{owner/repo}} |
| Cadence | {{hourly \| daily HH:MM \| weekdays HH:MM \| weekly \| one-off}} |
| Connectors | {{only what's needed, e.g. Slack, GitHub}} |
| Network | {{Trusted (default) \| Custom + allowed domains \| Full}} |

> Min interval is 1 hour. Recurring runs count against your **daily routine run
> cap**; one-off runs don't (they use normal subscription usage). Routines run
> autonomously with **no permission prompts** — scope repo, connectors, and
> network to exactly what's needed.

## Create it

### From the CLI (scheduled triggers)

```
/schedule {{cadence}}, use the {{AGENT_NAME}} agent to {{TASK}}
```

Examples:
```
/schedule daily at 9am, use the {{AGENT_NAME}} agent to {{TASK}}
/schedule in 2 weeks, use the {{AGENT_NAME}} agent to {{TASK}}   # one-off
```

`/schedule` requires a **claude.ai subscription login**. It's hidden if
`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`/`ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN`/`apiKeyHelper` is set, if
telemetry-off env vars are set, or if you're inside a Claude Code **web**
session — in those cases create it at https://claude.ai/code/routines instead.

### From the web (any trigger)

https://claude.ai/code/routines → **New routine** → set prompt, repo,
environment, and trigger. Add **API** (per-routine `/fire` endpoint + bearer
token) or **GitHub** (`pull_request.*` / `release.*`) triggers here — the CLI
makes scheduled triggers only.

## Verify

```
/schedule list          # confirm next-run time
/schedule run           # fire once now to smoke-test
```
A green run status means the session started cleanly, **not** that the task
succeeded — open the run transcript to confirm.
